b"Months following the start of lockdowns and isolation, it felt pointless to take care of myself. Even marching to the bathroom to take a shower felt like a task of herculean proportions. So perhaps having the desire to actually exercise self-care is a good sign. I'll take it."
b"It's Tony Sunday!!! #TonyAwards2022"

b'Over the course of the pandemic, my mental health took a hit, and it definitely improved once I headed to New York for work. One big sign for me that things were better was this: I started doing my nails again. Not getting them done, but doing them myself. No idea why though.'

b'Making more of an effort to stay on top of my paperwork. Over the last two years though, I found myself overwhelmed. It helped to set goals, and when I hit the ones I set for the day, it felt like an accomplishment.'

b'Those of us that have received closing notices understand only too well. Know that we all see you, get what you\xe2\x80\x99re feeling, raise you up and celebrate you.'

b'In both cases, we were allowed the space to mourn as a company and as individual human beings. I remember spacing out, searching for solace and comfort among friends, raising many toasts, and giving and getting lots of hugs. A closing feels like a death.'

b'When Flower Drum Song closed, our lead producer Ben Mordecai sat me down in my dressing room to tell me the show would be closing. For Allegiance, our PSM Peter Wolf announced over the loudspeaker that we\xe2\x80\x99d all be gathering on stage with our producers. It was a tearful goodbye.'
b'Sigh\xe2\x80\xa6 I remember whenever a show I happened to be in was closing, the producers notified us in person, whether individually or as a full company. Siiiiiiiiiiiiigh\xe2\x80\xa6'

b"A few cast members wrapped tonight, meaning I don't know if/when we'll see each other again, but I'm thankful for the little face time we got to have and the laughs we got to share. You're all rockstars! /end"

b"Had things been more on the efficient side, we wouldn't have had this rare opportunity to connect. COVID isolation took so much of that away, so that impromptu hang turned out to be something very special, one that I'll always hold in my heart."

b'The time was spent in deep conversation, almost to the point of confessional. We ended up opening ourselves and bonding, getting closer to one another as human beings and appreciating that fate brought us together.'

b"Yesterday was a long shoot day for a few members of the cast, what with intricate camera work and choreography. There was a longer wait for a few others, which is fine. That's the life on a film set. We accept it."

b"Now that I'm home safe and the weekend is officially upon us, I'm in the right headspace to share what my unexpected blessing is. (This might be a tl;dr situation, in which case you're welcome to skip this completely.)"
